[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":388},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F02\u002F03\u002Fpixijs-v5-00-intro-and-toc\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F02\u002F03\u002Fpixijs-v5-00-intro-and-toc\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F02\u002F03\u002Fpixijs-v5-00-intro-and-toc\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F02\u002F03\u002Fpixijs-v5-00-intro-and-toc\u002F":363,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F02\u002F03\u002Fpixijs-v5-00-intro-and-toc\u002F":372},"\u002Fjavascript\u002F20200203\u002F3949702627\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":52,"date":344,"description":345,"extension":346,"lang":347,"meta":348,"navigation":349,"path":350,"readingMinutes":351,"seo":352,"standalone":353,"stem":354,"tags":355,"tldr":360,"updated":344,"url":361,"__hash__":362},"content\u002Fen\u002FJavaScript\u002Fpixijs-v5-00-intro-and-toc.md","PixiJS V5 Tutorial (0) - Why I'm Doing This + Full Table of Contents","1001694669",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":335},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,30,33,36,40,43,56,59,62,66,74,323,327],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"This series is basically something I'm writing for the w3HexSchool Year-of-the-Rat full marathon ironman challenge run by HexSchool. For this first post, let me talk a bit about why I picked PixiJS.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"why-pixijs","Why PixiJS?",[17,25,26],{},"The main reason is that on one project I had to build a bunch of effects, and one section in particular had to use PixiJS. Since I didn't really understand the tech, I figured I'd just throw myself in the deep end during this challenge and force myself to learn it. My hope is that by the end I can at least reach the \"ohh, okay\" level — where I can read PixiJS source code and actually follow what's going on.",[17,28,29],{},"The other reason is I'm honestly pretty curious about the kind of effects PixiJS can produce. A lot of games are made with PixiJS too. And because I'd already poked at it a little during that project, I was even able to tweak some of the code in there. So... I figured I'd just give writing about it a shot.",[17,31,32],{},"I'm hoping I can fully complete all 40 weeks of the challenge and walk away with the Golden Horn Award (an actual physical trophy)!!!!!!",[17,34,35],{},"Either way, the end goal is the Golden Horn Award. (Here I come!)",[12,37,39],{"id":38},"before-you-start","Before You Start",[17,41,42],{},"For this series I'd recommend you already have a basic grasp of the following:",[44,45,46,50,53],"ul",{},[47,48,49],"li",{},"CSS & HTML",[47,51,52],{},"JavaScript",[47,54,55],{},"Canvas (if you've touched it at all, you'll have an easier time — but it's not required, since I came in without ever having used it.)",[17,57,58],{},"If you've got those down, I think you should be able to follow this series fine, because I also came in having never touched PixiJS and just researched everything online myself. Unless I write it really badly (which, I'll admit, I probably will).",[17,60,61],{},"But if you've already learned Canvas, then I think this'll feel really natural to you, because PixiJS itself is built on top of Canvas.",[12,63,65],{"id":64},"table-of-contents","Table of Contents",[67,68,71],"callout",{"title":69,"type":70},"Note","note",[17,72,73],{},"This section will keep getting updated.",[44,75,76,83,89,95,101,107,113,119,125,131,137,143,149,155,161,167,173,179,185,191,197,203,209,215,221,227,233,239,245,251,257,263,269,275,281,287,293,299,305,311,317],{},[47,77,78,82],{},[79,80,81],"a",{"href":3},"PixiJS V5 Tutorial (0) - Intro & Table of Contents"," (article in Mandarin)",[47,84,85,82],{},[79,86,88],{"href":87},"\u002Fjavascript\u002F20200210\u002F3949702627\u002F","PixiJS V5 Tutorial (1) - Setting Up PixiJS",[47,90,91,82],{},[79,92,94],{"href":93},"\u002Fjavascript\u002F20200217\u002F4014508881\u002F","PixiJS V5 Tutorial (2) - WebGL and Renderer